Package uk.co.terminological.rjava.types

Class RInteger

java.lang.Object
uk.co.terminological.rjava.types.RInteger
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, JNIPrimitive, RObject, RPrimitive
public class RInteger extends Object implements RPrimitive, JNIPrimitive
The integer wrapper handles the translation of R integers to Java Integer.class while the value is passed through the JNI interface as an unboxed primitive int. This class is largely needed to handle R NA values, and map them to Java nulls. If you are not using a structure (such as a list or vector) and you know the value is not NA you can substitute a primitive int instead of this.
